<p><img src="http://i560.photobucket.com/albums/ss44/leegao/site_logo.gif" style="border: 0px solid rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0px; text-align: center; display: block; float: left;"></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 85%;"><strong><em><span style="color: rgb(128, 0, 0);">AMX2D&nbsp;</span></em><span style="color: rgb(128, 0, 0);">was created by Lee in order to simplify Lua scripting in CS2D&nbsp;by refactoring commonly used functions and recursively single out particular functions with unique names in order to eliminate the needs of awkward functions such as&nbsp; the lua <span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 153);">string.sub()</span></span> and etc in order to determine what the commands will be partitioned down into.</span></strong></span></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="color: rgb(128, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 100%;"><strong>Find out more at <a href="http://amx2d.co.cc/" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 115%;">http://amx2d.co.cc/</span></a></strong></span></span></p>
